16/10/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov left Sunday (16 October) for a formal four-day visit to the United States, where he is expected to hold talks with his US counterpart George W. 
Bush. 
He is also scheduled to visit Chicago and Boston.
In other news, former Bulgarian King Simeon Saxe-Coburg has been re-elected as leader of the country's main centrist party, National Movement Simeon II. 
He was backed by all 800 delegates at the party's congress Saturday. 
(BNR, Focus - 16/10/05; bTV, Mediapool - 15/10/05)
